<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,258,967]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,834,859]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,475,834,859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylanicus">
<emphasis box="[323,475,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. zeylanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[605,718,836,859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pronus">
<emphasis box="[605,718,836,859]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. pronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the male genitalia characters, but differs in the shape of the aedeagal shafts and the basal processes. In 
<taxonomicName box="[636,786,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylanicus">
<emphasis box="[636,786,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. zeylanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the shafts are very broad at the base and inwardly curved at distal 
<number box="[244,293,907,931]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="0.33">0.33</number>
length whereas in 
<taxonomicName box="[503,614,908,931]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pronus">
<emphasis box="[503,614,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. pronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the shafts are uniform in width and not so curved in posterior view, but in lateral view the shafts in 
<taxonomicName box="[431,543,943,966]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pronus">
<emphasis box="[431,543,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. pronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are strongly sinuate which is not the case in 
<taxonomicName box="[1045,1195,942,967]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylanicus">
<emphasis box="[1045,1195,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. zeylanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
